[Student "S"]
{Interesting hand. Too bad these only come up in lessons and never at the table! You could jump right into Ace-asking but there is no rush so you say 2\S. Partner now rebids 2NT.  

Now you know all about partner's hand. 22-24 points, balanced. Now ask for Aces. If you agree that 4\C is Gerber here then that's what you should bid. If not, then you would have to use Blackwood. Partner answers 4\D.  

The 4\D reply says either zero or all four. Put your money on all four and bid 7NT.}

